  "headline": "Olympic Games History",
  "description": "The Olympic Games trace to ancient Greece (776 BCE, Olympia). Modern Olympics revived by Pierre de Coubertin (1896, Athens). Summer and Winter Games held every 4 years (with exceptions for world wars and 2020 COVID postponement). Motto: Citius, Altius, Fortius — Communiter (Faster, Higher, Stronger — Together).",
